    "We then employed LLM-critic to provide recommendations and identify recurring themes based on our analysis and category mapping.",
    "These LLM-generated suggestions were subsequently validated through manual review.",
    "This detailed examination allowed us to pinpoint distinct error patterns, leading to the identification of eight primary error categories.",
    "These issues were further organized into two main divisions: Reasoning Failures, which encompass errors arising from reasoning deficiencies, and Structural Limitations, which include structural issues within the knowledge graph.",
    "Reasoning Failures: Most failures stem from the LLMs' inability to reason correctly."
